Kyle Thomas Vassell (born 7 February 1993) is English-born Northern Irish professional footballer who plays as a striker for the Northern Ireland national football team.
He began his career as a youth at Norwich City  and Brentford, before embarking on a nomadic period in non-League football. He made his Football League debut for Peterborough United in 2013. He is a distant relative of Darius and Isaac Vassell.

response: Vassell was born to Jamaican parents and is a practising Christian. He credits his faith for his survival of a serious car accident. Vassell's cousin Isaac is also a footballer and currently plays for Cardiff City. He is married to Amani Rodriquez-Thomas, they have a daughter named Persia; Vassell's 2017 autobiography Road to Persia was titled for her. He is also a cousin of Cheltenham Town forward Kyle Vassell.
